policy. the han, however, are far from homogeneous and speak a wide variety of mutually unintelligible local "dialects"; which most linguists actually classify as different languages using more or less the same set of chinese characters. many of the minority ethnic groups have their own languages as well. contrary to popular belief, there is no single unified han chinese culture, and while they share certain common elements such as confucian and taoist beliefs, the regional variations in culture among the han ethnic group are actually very diverse. many customs and deities are specific to individual regions and even villages. celebrations 